TITLE: Biden to meet Mexican president as surge of illegal drugs and immigrants continue to cross border
SUMMARY: Mexican President, Andrés Manuel López Obrador is set to meet with President Joe Biden at the White House, Tuesday. Experts say that Biden needs to push AMLO on illegal immigration and the massive increase in illegal drugs crossing the border.

TITLE: Jill Biden slammed by Hispanic conservatives for speaking at 'Latinx IncluXion' event
SUMMARY: First lady Jill Biden faced ridicule from Hispanic Republicans on Monday after news broke she would be headlining a "Latinx IncluXion Luncheon" in Texas.

TITLE: Texas showdown: Beto O’Rourke to hold 70 campaign events in 49 days as he challenges GOP Gov. Greg Abbott
SUMMARY: Democratic gubernatorial nominee Beto O’Rourke next week will launch an ambitious 49-day campaign swing across Texas, as he challenges two-term Republican Gov. Greg Abbott.

TITLE: Biden gun control speech interrupted by father of Parkland shooting victim
SUMMARY: Manuel Oliver, the farther of a child who died during a mass shooting in 2018 interrupted Biden during a speech he was giving on the White House lawn on gun control.

TITLE: Medical board threatens to revoke certification of OBGYNs over abortion 'misinformation’
SUMMARY: The American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology (ABOG) said it will review reports of "dissemination of misinformation and disinformation" about abortion and COVID-19.

TITLE: Schumer preps final shot at passing reconciliation bill as summer session kicks off
SUMMARY: Senate Democrats, led by Sen. Chuck Schumer, face a tight deadline to pass their party-line reconciliation bill, with the August recess and campaign season coming soon.

TITLE: Biden points to importance of Saudi 'energy resources' despite saying he wouldn't ask for more oil
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden defended his upcoming trip to Saudi Arabia, highlighting the country's "vital" energy resources despite recently promising not to ask the nation for more oil.

TITLE: Pompeo: Biden calling Saudi Arabia a ‘pariah’ state is an ‘enormous mistake’
SUMMARY: Former U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo told Fox News that President Joe Biden has made an “enormous mistake” calling Saudi Arabia a “pariah” state.

TITLE: Florida Senate candidate Rep. Val Demings skips political event with Dem who wants to 'divest' in police
SUMMARY: Rep. Val Demings, running against Florida Sen. Marco Rubio, was scheduled to attend a political event with a politician who wants to "divest" in police, but she never showed.

TITLE: CatholicVote launches $3 million midterm ad campaign aimed at kicking Catholic Democrats out of office
SUMMARY: A conservative Catholic political group will spend millions targeting Catholic Democrats for departing from church teaching and not standing up to "radical liberals" attacking churches.

TITLE: George Soros, Hollywood megadonors bankroll Stacey Abrams' leadership PAC
SUMMARY: Stacey Abrams’ second attempt to unseat Georgia Republican Gov. Brian Kemp is enjoying millions of dollars in donations from George Soros and wealthy progressives outside the state.

TITLE: Majority of Democrats don't want Biden to run again in 2024, poll finds
SUMMARY: Nearly two-thirds of Democratic voters don't want Joe Biden to run again for president in 2024, a new poll has found, as his approval rating has sank to just 33%.

TITLE: Americans support abortion bans prohibited by Roe v. Wade but claim to support Roe - is media bias why?
SUMMARY: Polls show that a majority of Americans both support upholding Roe v. Wade and pre-viability restrictions on abortion that Roe v. Wade wouldn't allow.

TITLE: Fox News Power Rankings: GOP expected to take control of House
SUMMARY: Fox News Power Rankings predict Republicans will take control of the House with at least 225 forecasted seats after midterm elections this coming November.

TITLE: Cruz requests Garland testify on DOJ steps to protect Supreme Court justices after abortion decision
SUMMARY: Sen. Ted Cruz is demanding Attorney General Merrick Garland be called to testify before the Senate Judiciary Committee on safety measures the DOJ is taking to protect Supreme Court justices.

TITLE: Parents of Israeli-American teen killed in 2001 bombing seek meeting with Biden on upcoming Middle East trip
SUMMARY: Arnold and Frimet Roth,whose daughter Malki was killed in a 2001 terrorist attack in Jerusalem, are asking to meet with President Joe Biden during his trip to Israel this week.

TITLE: Biden, Schumer and Durbin sprint to fill judicial vacancies before possible GOP Senate takeover
SUMMARY: With Republicans aiming to take back the Senate in the November midterms, Democrats face a six-month dash to confirm as many federal judges as possible.

TITLE: Missouri Senate race: Trump rules out Vicky Hartzler endorsement, tells voters to 'forget' about her
SUMMARY: President Donald Trump did not endorse a candidate in the U.S. Senate race in Missouri but said voters could "forget" about Republican Rep. Vicky Hartzler.

TITLE: $15M in American Rescue Plan funds went to ‘anti-racism,’ ‘social activism’ programs for kids
SUMMARY: The Institute of Museum and Library Services awarded over $15 million in American Rescue Plan funds to programs pushing "anti-racism education" and "social activism."

TITLE: Chuck Schumer tests positive for COVID-19, will work remote as Senate reconvenes this week
SUMMARY: Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer has tested positive for COVID-19 and will work remotely as the Senate convenes this week.
